# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
# 
# [optional body]
# 
# [optional footer(s)]
# 
# Types:
#   feat:     New feature (Minor version bump)
#   fix:      Bug fix (Patch version bump)
#   perf:     Performance improvement (Patch version bump)
#   feat!:    Breaking change (Major version bump)
#   docs:     Documentation only (no release)
#   style:    Code style/formatting (no release)
#   refactor: Code restructuring (no release)
#   test:     Adding tests (no release)
#   ci:       CI/CD changes (no release)
#   chore:    Maintenance tasks (no release)
# 
# Examples:
#   feat: add user authentication
#   fix(backup): handle missing directories
#   feat!: remove deprecated API endpoints
#   
#   BREAKING CHANGE: API endpoint /old removed
# 
# Scope (optional): backup, filter, cli, config, docs, test, ci
# 
# Tips:
#   - Use imperative mood: "add" not "added" or "adds"
#   - Keep subject line â‰¤ 72 characters
#   - Explain WHY in body, not WHAT (code shows what)
#   - Reference issues: "fixes #123"
# 
# Remember: semantic-release handles versioning automatically!
# See docs/commit-message-guide.md for full guide
